\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. D. dedeana} Boiss. & Reuter in Boiss., {\i Voy. Bot. Midi Esp.} {\b 2}: 718 (1845) (incl. {\i D. cantabrica }Willk., {\i D. zapateri }Willk.). Densely pulvinate, with very woody stock; scape villous, elongating after flowering, rather lax in fruit. Petals 4-6 mm, white, broadly obovate, emarginate, much longer than the stamens. Silicula hispid; style c. 0·5 mm. 2n = 32. •{\i  Mountains of N. & E. Spain.} Hs.
