\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. D. heterocoma} Fenzl, {\i Pugillus} 13 (1842). Densely pulvinate, with narrow, hairy, incurved leaves; scape 3-10 cm, glabrous. Inflorescence becoming lax in fruit. Petals 5-6 mm, yellow, obovate-cuneate, much longer than the stamens. Silicula 3·5-5 × 3 mm, ovoid, inflated, densely hairy; style 0·5 mm.{\i  Karpathos.} Cr. ({\i Anatolia}.)
\par

