\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 20. D. corymbosa} R. Br. ex DC., {\i Reg. Veg. Syst. Nat.}{\b  2}: 343 (1821) ({\i D. bellii }Holm, {\i D. macrocarpa} Adams). Scape up to 15 cm. Leaves with stalked, stellate and branched hairs on lower surface. Petals 3·5-5 mm, bright or pale yellow; filaments slightly dilated at the base. Silicula hairy. Style 0·2-0·75 mm. {\i Spitsbergen.} Sb. ({\i Circumpolar}.)
\par

