\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 22. D. adamsii} Ledeb.,{\i  Fl. Ross.}{\b  1}: 147 (1842) ({\i D. oblongata} auct., non R. Br. ex DC.). Scape up to 20 cm in fruit, with more or less elongated infructescence. Leaves with stellate hairs on the lower surface. Petals 2-3 mm, scarcely longer than the sepals, pale yellow or cream. Silicula hairy; style up to 0·2 mm. {\i Spitsbergen.} Sb. ({\i Circumpolar}.)
