\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 25. D. sibirica} (Pallas) Thell.,{\i  Mitt. Bot. Mus. Zürich}{\b  28}: 318 (1906). Stem long, slender, creeping, producing erect or ascending scape with 8-20 yellow flowers. Leaves oblong-lanceolate, acute, variably clothed with appressed, medifixed hairs (also present towards the base of the scape). Petals 4-6 mm, obovate-cuneate, yellow with brownish veins; stamens 2-2·5 mm. Silicula 4-7·5 × 1·5-2 mm, oblong-ellipsoidal, often somewhat curved, glabrous; style 0·5-0·75 mm. 2n = 16.{\i  E. & C. Russia.} Rs(N, C, W) [Rs(B)].
