\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. DRABA. Caespitose biennials or perennials with erect flowering stems and variably hairy leaves, often canescent. Cauline leaves usually present. Flowers usually rather small; petals white or cream, longer than the stamens; filaments sometimes slightly dilated at the base.
\par

